        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-07-05T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-07-05T11:00:00-05:00" n="1527" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1527">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">102.22/7–649: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cabot</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-07-06T00:00:00+08:00">July 6, 1949—midnight.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 6—12:36 p. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2640. After 2 hours’ talk with police they are now (11:30 p. m.) trying to clear
                    ex-Navy employees from in front of building. We have agreed to send a
                    representative to discuss matter Friday but have made it clear that we cannot
                    accept arbitration, are only acting as intermediaries and will not negotiate
                    under threat of violence.</p>
                <p>Please inform Navy.</p>
                <p>Sent Department 2640; repeated Nanking 1462.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cabot</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
